11/04/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Public Order Minister George Voulgarakis kicks off a three-day official visit to the United States on Monday (11 April), His office says he will meet with senior administration officials well as officials from the CIA and FBI. The agenda will include issues related to bilateral co-operation, regional security in Southeast Europe, and the fights against organised crime, terrorism, money laundering and drug trafficking. 
In other news, Bulgarian President Georgi Parvanov arrived Monday in Thessaloniki for informal talks with Greek counterpart Karolos Papoulias. The meeting was initially planned for Friday but was put off due to the pope's funeral. (ANA - 10/04/05)
